-- South Africa's National Roads Agency Sells Bonds to Fund Freeway Projects
-- Garth Theunissen
-- 2010-07-07T12:27:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/south-africa-s-national-road-agency-sells-bonds-to-fund-freeway-projects.html

          
          
             The  South African National Roads
Agency Ltd.  sold 543 million rand ($71 million) of bonds to fund
road construction and improvements, said Rand Merchant Bank,
which helped arrange the sale with Absa Capital.  
 The bonds, which were issued under its Domestic Medium Term
Note Program, carry a full guarantee from the South African
government, Johannesburg-based RMB, a unit of FirstRand Ltd.,
said in an e-mailed statement today.  
 The roads agency sold 485 million rand of 9.75 percent
bonds due July 31, 2020, and 58 million rand of 5.5 percent
inflation-linked bonds due Dec. 23, 2023,  Gill Rain , a member of
the arranging team at RMB, said in a telephone interview.  
 “The bulk of the proceeds will be used to fund Sanral’s
toll road expansion plan in the Gauteng province,” said Rain.
“The sale was fully subscribed.”  
